Data Structures

Here are the data structures with brief descriptions:
APER_CFG_TInput parameters about the aperture, like the diameter, amplitude map, etc

ATM_CFG_TInput parameters for the atmospheric turbulence

cmatDouble complex matrix object contains 2-d arrays of double complex numbers

cspcell2-d array of csp

dspSparse array of double numbers stored in compressed column format, i.e
DTF_SDetector transfer function
DTF_TData associated with a detector transfer function for a subaperture
ETF_TData associated with an elongation transfer function for a subaperture
EVL_CFG_TContarins input parameters all evaluation directions
FDPCG_TData for Fourier Domain Preconditioner
file_tInformation about opened files
FIT_CFG_TInput parameters for deformable mirror fitting
INTSTAT_TIntensity statistics assiciated with a certain powfs
LLT_CFG_TInput parameters for laser launch telescope

MAP_TOPD or Amplitude map defined on square/rectangular grids
MOAO_CFG_TInput parameters for each MOAO type

mt_stateContains state of a random stream
MUV_TDecompose an operator into a sparse operator and optional low rank terms
NGSMOD_TNGS mode in ad hoc split tomography
PARMS_TWrapper of all _CFG_T data types
PISTAT_SStruct for pixel intensity statistics
PLAN1D_TAn arrays of 1-d plans that are used to do 2-d FFTs only over specified region
PLOT_CFG_TInput parameters for plotting during simulation
POWFS_CFG_TInput parameters for each type of wfs (powfs)

POWFS_TData associated with a certain type of WFS
PTS_TLow left point of each subaperture
